---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Installation" description="How to install MeasureKit with pip, uv, or from source" activeSection="install">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="kicker">Getting Started</div>
    <h1>Installation</h1>
    <p>MeasureKit has zero runtime dependencies in the base install. Optional extras add backends and acceleration.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>From PyPI</h2>
  <p>Choose the install that matches your use case:</p>

  <div class="install-options">
    <div class="install-option">
      <div class="option-header">
        <span class="option-title">Minimal</span>
        <span class="badge badge-green">Recommended to start</span>
      </div>
      <p>Pure-Python, zero runtime dependencies. Works everywhere Python 3.10+ runs.</p>
      <div class="tabs">
        <div class="tab-list">
          <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="pip-min">pip</button>
          <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="uv-min">uv</button>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel active" id="pip-min">
          <pre><code>pip install measurekit</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" id="uv-min">
          <pre><code>uv add measurekit</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="install-option">
      <div class="option-header">
        <span class="option-title">With Rust Acceleration</span>
        <span class="badge badge-blue">Highly recommended</span>
      </div>
      <p>Adds the <code>measurekit-core</code> Rust extension (via PyO3) for faster eager-mode scalar operations.</p>
      <div class="tabs">
        <div class="tab-list">
          <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="pip-native">pip</button>
          <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="uv-native">uv</button>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel active" id="pip-native">
          <pre><code>pip install "measurekit[native]"</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" id="uv-native">
          <pre><code>uv add "measurekit[native]"</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="install-option">
      <div class="option-header">
        <span class="option-title">Full Install</span>
        <span class="badge badge-yellow">All backends</span>
      </div>
      <p>NumPy, PyTorch, JAX, SymPy, Pandas, Pydantic, h5py, and the Rust core — everything included.</p>
      <div class="tabs">
        <div class="tab-list">
          <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="pip-all">pip</button>
          <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="uv-all">uv</button>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel active" id="pip-all">
          <pre><code>pip install "measurekit[all]"</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" id="uv-all">
          <pre><code>uv add "measurekit[all]"</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Optional extras</h2>
  <p>You can mix and match extras as needed:</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Extra</th>
        <th>Includes</th>
        <th>Use when</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>native</code></td>
        <td>measurekit-core (Rust)</td>
        <td>You want faster eager-mode scalars</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>numpy</code></td>
        <td>NumPy, SciPy, Numba, jaxtyping</td>
        <td>Working with arrays</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>torch</code></td>
        <td>PyTorch, jaxtyping</td>
        <td>PyTorch tensor support + JIT</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>jax</code></td>
        <td>JAX, jaxlib, jaxtyping</td>
        <td>JAX array support + jit/vmap</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>pandas</code></td>
        <td>pandas ≥ 2.2</td>
        <td>Pandas extension support</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>symbolic</code></td>
        <td>SymPy, symengine</td>
        <td>Symbolic differentiation</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>pydantic</code></td>
        <td>Pydantic ≥ 2.10</td>
        <td>Validation in Pydantic models</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>io</code></td>
        <td>h5py, pyarrow, xarray, netCDF4</td>
        <td>Save/load quantity states</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>rich</code></td>
        <td>Rich ≥ 13</td>
        <td>Pretty terminal output</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Verify your installation</h2>
  <pre><code>python -c "import measurekit; print(measurekit.__version__)"
# 0.1.8</code></pre>

  <p>Or try the quick demo:</p>
  <pre><code>python -m measurekit "9.81 m/s^2 * 70 kg => N"
# 686.7 N</code></pre>

  <h2>Building from source</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-warning">
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Building from source requires the Rust toolchain. You only need this for development or custom Rust extensions.</p>
  </div>

  <ol class="steps">
    <li>
      <div>
        <h3>Install prerequisites</h3>
        <p>You need Rust (via <a href="https://rustup.rs" target="_blank" rel="noopener">rustup</a>), Python 3.10+, and <code>uv</code>.</p>
        <pre><code># Install Rust
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh

# Install uv
pip install uv</code></pre>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <h3>Clone and build the Rust core</h3>
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/Alexisrx96/measurekit
cd measurekit

# Build and install the Rust extension
cd measurekit_core
maturin develop --release
cd ..</code></pre>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <h3>Install in editable mode</h3>
        <pre><code># Install with all extras + dev tools
pip install -e ".[all]"</code></pre>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <h3>Run the tests</h3>
        <pre><code>pytest tests/</code></pre>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Requirements</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Version</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Python</td><td>≥ 3.10</td><td>Tested on 3.10, 3.11, 3.12, 3.13, 3.14</td></tr>
      <tr><td>pip</td><td>any recent</td><td>Or uv, poetry, etc.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Rust (optional)</td><td>stable</td><td>Only needed for <code>[native]</code> from source</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="next-section">
    <a href="/quickstart" class="btn-primary">Next: Quick Start →</a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .install-options { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
  .install-option {
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .option-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .option-title { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); }
  .install-option p { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .install-option .tabs { margin: 0; }
  .install-option pre { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent); color: white;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem; border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
    display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--accent2); text-decoration: none; }
  .next-section { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
</style>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-list').forEach(tabList => {
    const tabs = tabList.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn');
    tabs.forEach(tab => {
      tab.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const targetId = tab.getAttribute('data-tab');
        tabs.forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
        tab.classList.add('active');
        const container = tabList.closest('.tabs');
        container?.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel').forEach(panel => {
          panel.classList.toggle('active', panel.id === targetId);
        });
      });
    });
  });
</script>
